			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hiya:
<br />

<br />
27 Red Mage here.
<br />

<br />
I solo most evens (Not All.. and its getting harder... at 22 I took toughs).
<br />
I carry a Flame Sword and Heater Shield... Good armor with some resist stuff
<br />

<br />
I have up Protect,Shell, and get FM
<br />
Then cast Flame Spikes,En(Element),Regeneration... Sometimes A Bar(Element) depending on the foe. THEN I open the fight
<br />

<br />
I open the fight by attack (From beyond sword range) and then pull with a cast to get the monster to com in to range and take an instant smack
<br />

<br />
My Casting Sequence is
<br />
Paralyze,Slow,Dia,Blind,
<br />

<br />
If the Monster is Lower than even I dont bother to Slow or Blind unless the fight is not going smoothly.
<br />

<br />
I Dont bother with poison or Bio.. The Same mana =CureII=82 Hit points
<br />
which turns in to several strikes of the sword... Far More damage than the DOT spells would do.
<br />

<br />
SOMETIMES I use an apropriate nuke but that mana too goes better to healing. USUALY. I Nuke at the end of a fight I know I have won in order toraise the Elemental skills.
<br />

<br />
My favorite sub classes are White (Max Groupage and combat durability)
<br />
and Warrior.. Cuz You can take a lickin and keep on ticken without pausing to heal so much mid fight(giving the mob free shots at you)
<br />

<br />

<br />
For you Red mages that cant get groups worry not... Solo but be sure to not focus on the ez stuff or your skills will lag...get groups when you can and get rich.. remember soloing you get ALL THE LOOT. which means ohh about 6 times as much as in a group.
<br />

<br />
At 20th I had the best stuff skill caps would let me wear and 30 K I could
<br />
NOT SPEND on anything I could use... LITERALY.
<br />

<br />
I recomend Heater Sheild and Flame Sword as your weapons of Choice... when you level to that point.. then watch the mobs fall at your feet.
<br />

<br />
We may not be the most popular in a group but if you Red Mage has trouble getting a group think about being a theif...
<br />

<br />
Ne Way.. soon your troubles will be over... By the high teens you will be in high demand. Mostly as a healer but hey... They have no clue that you can out damage a Dark Knight at that level.
<br />

<br />
Stormsong.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
