				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">rdm or whm?
<br />

<br />
really?
<br />

<br />
from 12-20 you can pass off as a whm, not much diffrent, more downtime for your pt but if you cant find a whm then you can do the job, 
<br />

<br />
from 21-30 your debuffs and dots are more powerful, but again, you can still pull off an okay whm, still downtime
<br />

<br />
from 31-35 debuffs are needed and appreciated, yes you can still do it you can still pretend to be a whm, more down time
<br />

<br />
from 36-40 yes you can but thats one desparate PT, I personally would disband the PT, and look for one with a smn/whm or a whm/anything(yes even a whm/nin would be preferable)
<br />

<br />
from 41-50 pure gravy, the only debuff that counts is dispel, the only enhance that counts is refresh, believe me your MP is better spent on these two spells than any other in your list. no one in thier right mind will ask you to be a primary healer, unless there is two RDM's in the PT, and they take turns one heal other debuff/dot, and they swap roles and convert on will
<br />

<br />
51-75 no clue, really, and in theory its going to be like 41-50, 
<br />
or so my jpn friends say, ^^
<br />

<br />
Gasgul TaruTaru 50RDM</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
